ic novels: Native Son by Richard Wright, Invisible Man by Ralph Ellison, The Bluest Eye and Song of Solomon by Toni Morrison, and Corregidora by Gayl Jones.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aAfrican American families in literature. 0aAfrican American women in literature. 0aAfrican Americans in literature. 0aAfrican AmericansxIntellectual life. 0aAmerican fictionxAfrican American authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aDomestic fiction, AmericanxHistory and criticism. 0aDwellings in literature. 0aFamilies in literature. 0aHome in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / African-American.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044247240uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/prin1344040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231508797423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231508797/original  a978-3-11-044247-2  Columbia University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK